title: For Sale:  Maadi (Egyptian Army) AK-47 build kit 7.62x39
postcontent:
Bought this late last year for a project I had in mind.  Since then, something completely different fell in my lap and now I don't need it!

If the ad is up, it is for sale.  This is an incomplete fire arm.

Ak-47 7.62x39 Maadi (Egyptian Army) parts kit.  Egyptian AK's are made on Russian equipment in Cairo, and are considered as close to a Russian AKM as you can get.  (That means they are very good quality).  Do your due internet research.  Or if you are a builder and already know what's what, never mind. :D

The Egyptian AK's are sought after for the Egyptian lettering on the rear sight and on the barrel trunion.  The 'crutch' stock (sidefolder) is also highly sought after by collectors (says the internet).  They are perfect for someone who wants a REALLY good AK, but doesn't want an Arsenal like everybody else.

All numbers I can see are matching.  It does not appear to have been fired much, if at all, based on my untrained eye's view of the bolt face.

When this arrived in the mail, the bag had popped, so I removed all the parts, got most of the cosmo off of them and re-applied a healthy dose of lithium grease mixed with synthetic oil.  The barrel trunion has light surface rust.  This can easily be remedied with treatment before building, does not affect function, and is just a fact of life with the bare steel.

All parts included are what was shipped to me.  All parts are represented in the pictures.  I haven't built an AK before and was going to have this pro built, so if you don't see a part, it probably didn't come with it.

  There is no barrel, no receiver.  There are a few chopped up bits of receiver in the upper right.


Price is firm, prefer FTF but will ship with DISCREET paypal.  This is not a firearm, but prefer local sale to resident who doesn't creep me out.

If interested, respond with availability to meet and your suburb so I can cut out about 10 emails back and forth about where and when :)
